<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-206-091 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 424 438</DOCID><JOURNAL>Information Week  March 4 1991 n310 p17(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Blockbuster expansion: leading U.S. video chain uses IT to winmarket share. (Blockbuster Entertainment Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Violino, Robert.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Blockbuster Entertainment Corp started out as Cook Data Services,a Dallas-based company selling software to the oil and gasindustry.andP;  The name change came about when the founder decided toabandon the software business and open a video rental store inDallas.andP;  Blockbuster Video now dominates the US video rentalarena.andP;  The company already has stores in the United Kingdom,Canada and Mexico and plans to expand to Australia, Japan,Ireland, Spain and Venezuela.andP;  The company's 120-personinformation systems (IS) department will play a major role in thatexpansion.andP;  IS technology has contributed to efficient customerservice for the company by implementing a bar code laser scanningsystem to expedite checkout procedures.andP;  Company officials statethat Blockbuster was probably one of the first chains outside thegrocery industry to use bar codes in a retail setting.andP;  Bar codesalso help track the ever-changing inventory.andP;  Customer credit andtransaction reporting processes have also been automated.andP;  Eachstores has a Digital Equipment MicroVAX 3100 or MicroVAX 2000minicomputer and VT-320 terminals.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Blockbuster Entertainment Corp. (Data processing)Digital Equipment Corp. (Products).andO;Ticker:    DEC; BV.andO;Product:   DEC MicroVAX 3100 (Minicomputer) (Usage)DEC MicroVAX 2000 (Minicomputer) (Usage)DEC VT320 (Computer terminal) (Usage).andO;Topic:     Information Resources ManagementBar-Code ScannersVideo IndustryRentingRetailing.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>